        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2615036953" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9239509744805402197">I didn&apos;t find this book reasonable. She made assumptions without proving them and made interpretations of certain verses of the Qur&apos;an which made me wonder how she understood them that way. Yes, we shouldn&apos;t attach too much to worldy things, but does this mean that we weren&apos;t created for this world? Imperfect humans for a perfect thereafter? As far as I know, we were created for this Dunya to make it a better place. Maybe she means that but it wasn&apos;t clear in her book, like other things which we</span>
  <span id="freeText9239509744805402197" style="display:none">I didn't find this book reasonable. She made assumptions without proving them and made interpretations of certain verses of the Qur'an which made me wonder how she understood them that way. Yes, we shouldn't attach too much to worldy things, but does this mean that we weren't created for this world? Imperfect humans for a perfect thereafter? As far as I know, we were created for this Dunya to make it a better place. Maybe she means that but it wasn't clear in her book, like other things which were not so clear. <br />I didn't complete the book so my review is on the part that I read.</span>
